      "step_index": 1,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Basic center:** one **tertiary amine** (the `N3` in a bridged/bicyclic amine). This is a classic CYP2D6 inhibition motif because it is **protonatable at physiological pH** and can engage the CYP2D6 \u201cacidic anchor\u201d (Asp301).\n- **Ring systems:** a **rigid polycyclic/bridged framework** (tropane-like / azabicyclic character). Rigid cationic bicyclic amines are commonly recognized by CYP2D6.\n- **Oxygenated functionality:** **lactone/ester** (`C(=O)O`), plus an additional **ester substituent** (`COC(=O)\u2026`), and **alcohol(s)** (two OH groups). These increase polarity and H-bonding but don\u2019t remove basicity.\n- **Aromatic rings:** **none**. This is important because many strong CYP2D6 inhibitors have at least one **lipophilic aromatic ring** to occupy the hydrophobic pocket.\n- **Structural alert check:** contains a **tertiary amine** (alert present), but **not quinidine-like** (no aromatic/quinoline system).",
      "tool_name": null,
