      "content": "### 3) CONSIDER mechanistic basis (how it would interact with CYP2D6)\n- Likely binding mode (if it inhibits): **protonated tertiary amine** engages **Asp301** (key recognition element), while the rigid bicyclic scaffold provides shape complementarity.\n- However, **absence of an aromatic \u201chydrophobic anchor\u201d** means it may not achieve the residence time/pose stabilization typical of clinically relevant CYP2D6 inhibitors.",
